CatDescriptText: There was a door under the pulpit of the church into this chamber.  The chamber might have originally been used for cooling, though it was thought to have also been used as part of the Underground Railroad as a route to the canal.
TitMainTitle: Man standing in brick arched vault, possibly an Underground Railroad refuge, below Avery Memorial A.M.E.Z. Church at Nash and Avery Streets on the North Side
